The _Compare_ template parameter actually must be a _type_. See [documentation](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/named_req/Compare).

Defining it like this is the correct way to do it:

    struct myComparator
    {
        bool operator()(const pair&lt;double, int&gt; &amp;a, const pair&lt;double, int&gt; &amp;b)
        {
            return a.first &lt; b.first;
        }
    };

Note also that the parameters must be const references to properly meet the requirements for Compare.


  [1]: https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/named_req/BinaryPredicate

